{"title": "Thanatopsis", "description": "LibriVox volunteers bring you 11 recordings of Thanatopsis by William Cullen Bryant.<br>\r\n\r\nThis was the Fortnightly Poetry project for April 12, 2022.<br>\r\n-----<br>\r\nThe author was only 18 when he wrote this contemplation on death, his most famous poem. His teenage musings on nature's capacity to delight us and calm us while we live, then enfold us -- every one of us -- in its bosom for all eternity, captures a serene truth. The earth is a giant graveyard and a consummate leveler, for everybody suffers the same fate in the end. (Summary by Michele Fry)", "duration": 3541, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1343", "name": "William Cullen Bryant"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/thanatopsis_2204.poem_librivox/thanatopsis_2204.jpg", "copyright_year": "1854", "genres": ["Multi-version (Weekly and Fortnightly poetry)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Michele Fry"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Michele Fry"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Thanatopsis - read by APS", "readers": [13577], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thanatopsis_2204.poem_librivox/thanatopsis_bryant_aps_64kb.mp3", "duration": 321}, {"section": 2, "title": "Thanatopsis - read by BK", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thanatopsis_2204.poem_librivox/thanatopsis_bryant_bk_64kb.mp3", "duration": 323}, {"section": 3, "title": "Thanatopsis - read by CD", "readers": [2733], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thanatopsis_2204.poem_librivox/thanatopsis_bryant_cd_64kb.mp3", "duration": 322}, {"section": 4, "title": "Thanatopsis - read by LKA", "readers": [16550], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thanatopsis_2204.poem_librivox/thanatopsis_bryant_kla_64kb.mp3", "duration": 391}, {"section": 5, "title": "Thanatopsis - read by KS", "readers": [13278], "pa